org.eclipse.papyrus.infra.services.tracepoints.preferences

Class BinaryEncodedMChoiceFieldEditor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.jface.preference.FieldEditor
      • org.eclipse.papyrus.infra.services.tracepoints.preferences.MultipleChoiceFieldEditor
        • org.eclipse.papyrus.infra.services.tracepoints.preferences.BinaryEncodedMChoiceFieldEditor

  • public class BinaryEncodedMChoiceFieldEditor
extends MultipleChoiceFieldEditor
    A class derived from the MultipleChoiceFieldEditor. It encodes a multiple choice value in a binary way, i.e. bit I is set in the result, if the i-th choice is active. This class can also be used outside a preference page
    Author:
    ansgar
